title: For Sale:  AK Norinco 56 Pre-Ban Rifle
postcontent: If you've seem my LMT you know the Queen of my collection.  I invite you to meet the King.  This is a rare early import pre-ban Norinco 56 AK pattern rifle.  All of my research suggests this rifle was imported through California and likely was seem in some movie.  These early import Chinese AK's have no markings indicating country of origin other than the "56" on the left side of the receiver and therefore were used to emulate Russian AK's in movies. There are no other obvious markings that would stand out on the big screen.  This rifle has a threaded barrel, high quality Texas Weapons Systems railed top cover, and Texas Weapons Systems rear sight.  Ask anyone in the AK community and they will tell you Norinco 56's are one of the best and most reliable.  I struggled long and hard about parting with this rifle.  In the end this King needs to sing and I don't have time to book him right now.  Do you?  Take a look at what Norinco 84's are going for on GB and the 84 is the little brother to the 56  This is your chance to own a piece of quality history and one you can bet your life on before he goes on the road to Utah on 10/27/16.  Of course this rifle is Semi-Automatic in 7.62x39.  Should you choose to manage this king I will also include 500rds of Brown Bear 7.62x39 Ammo.  As usual this rifle is only for sale to those legally allowed to own.

postcontent: have a like-new in box (LNIB) mint condition SCAR 16 in black. I purchased it brand new a few months ago and have only taken it to the range 3 times. And so I picked this up a few months ago to give it a whirl. But once a precision shooter, always a precision shooter...it just kinda hurts my eyes to look at paper groups bigger than 1/4 inch at 100 yards. title: For Sale:  SCAR 16
postcontent: have a like-new in box (LNIB) mint condition SCAR 16 in black. I purchased it brand new a few months ago and have only taken it to the range 3 times. It has only 270-300 rounds through it, ie, I put maybe 9 or 10 mags through it, and that's all. The gun functions flawlessly, it looks brand new with barely a single scratch or smudge, and it shot anything I put through it without a single jam or FTF or FTE. It produces average 5 shot groups around 1.0 - 1.5 inches at 100 yards when scoped, and could probably do a bit better with a proper load work-up, as I was just using factory ammo. I have the Geissele SuperSCAR 2-stage trigger already installed, which breaks very nicely at around 4 pounds. I'm selling this gem simply because as cool as it is, and as flawless as it is for what it is, this is just not my type of thing... In terms of rifle shooting I'm really just an old school benchrest guy, but had thought I would try my hand at AR style shooting for the first time ever. And so I picked this up a few months ago to give it a whirl. But once a precision shooter, always a precision shooter...it just kinda hurts my eyes to look at paper groups bigger than 1/4 inch at 100 yards. I guess you gotta know who you are in life and stick with it: So when the zombie apocalypse comes, I'll be best utilized by my tribe standing off at distance, methodically taking out targets with my high-precision rigs :) ... others will be better utilized for the CQB spray and pray type of work. :) We gotta be who we are :) The gun will come with the Geissele trigger already installed, and the attached UTG bipod I'll just throw in.
